The paper discusses a new scheme for reducing the energy cost of Proof-of-Work in cryptocurrencies, which is a topic related to computer security (cs.CR) and distributed computing (cs.DC). The scheme also involves the use of empty blocks to achieve scalability, which is a topic related to data structures (cs.DS) and game theory (cs.GT). Finally, the paper presents a theoretical analysis of the scheme's properties, which is a topic related to social and information networks (cs.SI).
